<br>
feel free to ask more questions, lots of great folks around here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ujarnsyngva.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnsyngva</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/29/02 6:03:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> 2H definitely for the higher damage! If you want more defense, spec higher in parry since that works with 2H weapon. My template at level 50 is 46BS/40Hammer/25Parry. Most skalds go with lower parry since it is not as effective in RvR as in PvE. Depends on your playstyle though - I like the higher parry and won't respec <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>~Jarnsyngva~  50 skald of Hrafn Gjalla, Palomides</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uturittruehammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turit Truehammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/29/02 7:13:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> Be ready to go either way.<br>
<br>
One handed vs two handed.. unlike my other Skald companions I will use them depending on what I am fighing or who I am fighting with to be more to the point.<br>
<br>
If you blindly go with two handed then you are taking some flexabality away from yourself.  This is how it works for me, and I must say it works very very well.<br>
<br>
One handed.<br>
 I go one handed with sheild if I am duoing with my partner.  This way we can ping pong the agro if we have to.  Also, keep your dex up there and you WILL block alot.  During a fight with a yellow con and even alot of lower orange cons *I am 41 at this time*, I will either block, parry, evade or they will miss outright very close to half the time.  I block way more than I evade and parry more then I block.<br>
<br>
  Also, if I am in a group where I am not to be the main tank, I like one handed because there is a much smaller chance that I will take the agro when I am not suppose to.  Nothing like taking agro and getting yelled at for doing it when you were not suppose to.*LOL*<br>
<br>
Two handed<br>
<br>
  I use two handed in RvR and when I solo.  Basically, you kill alot faster than if you are using a one handed.  The few times I will switch mid fight and go back to one handed is if I am fighting a stealth class *exclude the stupid Alb minstrals*  Because of there evade and duel weilding *or one handed and sheild* I like to use the one handed so a miss is not so bad.  I will switch back to two handed when they are at 25% health.  If you do not like switching back and forth, then just stick with the two handed all the way.<br>
<br>
  There ya go... something else to think about.*grin* <p>Rodog<br><br>

*fast as fast can be... unless I see a burger joint, then you can find me there*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufenrisfil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fenrisfil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/30/02 6:40:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> Well shield using skalds got a major boost with realm abilities. They can now actually improve their blocking rate from the base 5% which makes it much more worth while. You need aug dex 2, so you may as well also get mastery of pain to improve crit chances, and then you should be looking pretty reasonable.<br>
<br>
Anyway, personally I carry around both. For RvR I *only* use 2 handed (even though my 1 hander looks cooler at the moment, heh). For PvE it depends on the situation. When soloing I always use a 2 hander, when in a small group it depends on if I've become the main tank or not. If I am tanking I'll use the sheild. For a large group I will almost always go 1 hander, because this usually involved fighting purples and 2 handers are just too slow against purple (too inconsistant with the miss rate against purples being so high). Of course sometimes with large groups you are fighting reds and bellow, just in larger numbers, in those cases (when not being the main tank) I probably would still use  a 2 hander.<br>
<br>
I learned fairly early on that a skald swining at a purple with a 2 hander is a bad idea. I guess it may be better if you are max weapon specced though. <br>
<br>
Anyway do remember with a skald it's less of an either/or as you can do both. Warriors if they use shield will spec highly in shield, and as such mean if they switch to a 2 hander they are wasting half their points.  I suppose if a skald does choose mastery of blocking 5 (which would give a base 20% to block the same as speccing to 31 in shield (without the styles though)) then they would be wasting a lot of realm skill points if they switch back so would be similar to a warriors situation. You could certainly afford to put in 4 pts to get it to +6% and then be a pretty flexible skald without limiting yourself.<br>
<br>
Btw, the last word I heard on blocking in RvR is that when you are doing a style yourself it lowers your chance to block (possibly just when your opponent is doing a style too). That was off Sanya at E3. So blocking does work in RvR but you have to be willing to not use styles, which with a one hander would lower your damamge quite a lot. However it may make sense if you have your +6% blocking to switch to 1h and shield when you are out of endurance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uclapperoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Clapperoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/30/02 3:18:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> Both is the only real answer.  It's silly to restrict yourself to one way.  I use my 2H when I want to take some of the aggro or fights will be very quick (Malm pulls, big RvR battles) since it hits in one big foop.  I use my 1h when fighting uber-high purples since the % gain of our damage add is more effective (note:  always use your fastest weapon against Legion.  Damage add will do far more damage than your base).<br>
<br>
And the part that many people forget is:  many shields have valuable stat bonuses that you can get from a slot you ordinarily don't use.  If I could throw a stat bonus item into my ranged slot, I would.  Since the dps of both my 1h and 2h are 16.1 (at the moment), I can use my shield slot for 20-25 bonus stat points.<br>
<br>
For lower levels I would also mention that the shield is awfully nice while soloing - we can't spec it but I recall blocking at least once in most fights against yellows.  Sometimes one hit worth of protection is the difference between life and death. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvnomdarock.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vnom Da Rock</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/30/02 3:32:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> Both <br>
<br>
I would much prefer to miss at 2.5 seconds then miss at 4.5 second swings.<br>
So fighting purple cons I always go one hander cause I hate to not only miss but also miss the damage add.<br>
at least with the one hander I may hit smaller but the extra swings add up in damage add.<br>
Plus what all the other things people have said so far.<br>
 <p>Vnom Da Rock
Screaming Skald
Einherjar


"Never argue with an idiot, they will drag you to there level and beat you with experience."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uakrux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akrux</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/30/02 4:52:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> RvE:<br>
There is a significant bonus to damage output for using a 2hand weapon.  You would need a serious reason to give up that extra damage output in RvE.  A possibility is a healing limited group with you as the only tank.  Say a group consists of skald, shaman, 2 x runie, sb and hunter.  With a shield you use less shaman healing power but the group still kills the mob in almost exactly the same amount of time.  You would need protect on the shaman to keep the aggro with a shield limiting your damage output.  However in my opinion this situation is so rare that it is not worth carrying a decent 1hand weapon and shield around for it.<br>
<br>
99%+ of the time you will be using a 2hand weapon.<br>
<br>
RvR:<br>
It is true that if you are carrying a shield then an archer is less likely to attack you.  However you have the tools to survive an archer attack (and to kill the archer) and better that they attack you then a realmmate who will die to the archer.  You should be happy to get targetted by an archer.  <br>
<br>
The higher damage output of the 2hand weapon is the main reason I always go 2hand in RvR.<br>
<br>
Another factor is that at level 50 getting your hands on a top level 50 1hand weapon and shield is possibly depriving a realmmate of the same items.  <br>
<br>
Akrux Adanac<br>
Skald 50 Kay <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/31/02 2:38:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> The objective answer is : two handers are better, peridod, because skalds are unspecced in shields, and 2-handers have a built in bonus to parry and dmg over a 1-hander.<br>
<br>
That beeing said, 1-handers have a situational use, and I regulary use one : the shield can block a few arrows in certain RvR circumstances, the shield can have some nifty pluses, but the most compelling argument of choosing 1-handed in some difficult fights is that you are less dependant on &quot;luck&quot; (a miss with a quick weapon has less of an impact on a given combat than a miss with a slow weapon, even if it's the same average DPS in the long run).<br>
<br>
Dargaard, 41 Skald <p>---------
