<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=80615">Megh   Les Princes de Sarnar</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uindevla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Indevla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/31/02 12:12:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> I've heard that 2H actually parries more than 1H. Some people have told me that parry is more effective with a 2 hander....<br>
<br>
Is it actually more effective? meaning that a character will parry more often with a 2H than a 1H? If this is the case, then how much more effective is it? have tests been run?<br>
<br>
Maybe what has happened is that i've misunderstood what people have meant. Are they simply saying that because a 2 hander doesn't have a shield that the same percentage of parrying turns out to be 100% of their defense rather than having some blocks.<br>
<br>
I think i've posed my question pretty clearly....but maybe i haven't.<br>
