<br>
plus i can draw aggro off my healer friends alot easier when needed, if you want one of those &quot;function over fashion&quot; reasons<br>
<br>
if i got guard and engage it would be a whole diff story, but i dont... <p>------------------- <br>
E: 44 skald in tristan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uakrux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akrux</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/5/02 11:42:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> Originally posted by Kjeld:<br>
&quot;2-handers have a built in bonus to parry and dmg over a 1-hander.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sorry but this is half wrong.  There is a definite bonus to damage from using a 2hand weapon versus 1hand.  My best guess on this bonus is 10-15%.  This more than makes up for the 5% blocks from an unspecced shield.  If anyone knows a reliable source for the true 2hand damage bonus please post it here.<br>
<br>
However there is no bonus to parry.  In fact for a very long time there was a 50% penalty to parry % for 2hand users.  It took a lot of logs to prove this to Mythic but it was proven.  Mythic has stated that they have fixed the bug.  I am not sure I believe them.  As well, there is no parry against styles used by an enemy in RvR which limits the usefulness of parry.  The simple fact is that I very rarely hear the sound of a parry in RvR and I have 17 in parry for a parry chance of 13.5%.<br>
<br>
If you talk with a lot of experienced RvR skalds they will tell you that on respec they are planning to go from the standard 46s 44w 17p to something like 44s 49w 4p.  They just do not get the value from the points that they spent on parry.<br>
<br>
Akrux Adanac<br>
Skald 50 Kay<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufenrisfil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fenrisfil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/6/02 6:35:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> There is a lot of dispute of the attack resoloution order, but if block comes before parry, then obviously you'll parry more with a 2 hander simply because you won't be blocking.<br>
<br>
Other then that I'm not aware of any parry bonus with 2 handers. Indeed until recently parrying with 2 handers was bugged. Now that's been fixed it should be the same as 1 handers.<br>
<br>
A lot of 1 hand swords I've seen have +parry on (my current one does for example), where as 2 handers tend to have have str bonuses for more damamge. Also sheilds tend to have +hits, so chances are even if your not blocking much you'll have a better defence with a sheild set up.<br>
<br>
It's always worth carrying both anyway even if your don't plan to use one of the two styles. The exception I'd say is if you have spent a lot on mastery of blocking, then you should stick to 1handers so as to not waste the points (like a high sheild spec warrior). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufenrisfil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fenrisfil</A> at: 6/6/02 9:20:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/6/02 8:09:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> I used 2hander 90% of the time. In PvE group environment you dont want to take aggro if there are better tanks in the group. However it can be very hard for other classes to keep aggro from a 2h wielding skald. So I switch to 1h in those cases.<br>
<br>
RvR: Bubble chants. 1h weap will get in there -- 2h weap wont.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/umbolme.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mbolme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/6/02 10:40:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> &gt; There is a definite bonus to damage from using a 2hand weapon versus <br>
&gt; 1hand. My best guess on this bonus is 10-15%.<br>
<br>
I have not seen tests, but have heard from many sources that the bonus is 15% for Midgard and higher for other realms (because Midgard does not have to spec in 2-handed.)<br>
<br>
&gt; This more than makes up for the 5% blocks from an unspecced shield. <br>
<br>
Yes, especially, because while you are meleeing, you are always attacking, but not always being hit. It is true that you can get some bonuses from the shield though, and also faster weapons can get through bladeturn.<br>
<br>
&gt; In fact for a very long time there was a 50% penalty to parry % for <br>
&gt; 2hand users. <br>
<br>
This is true, because you were supposed to have a 50% penalty to parrying the 2-handed weapon. The coder got it backwards, and gave you a 50% penalty  to parrying with a 2-hander. As I now understand it, it is harder to parry a 2-hander attack. I have seen no logs to prove it, though.<br>
<br>
&gt; As well, there is no parry against styles used by an enemy in RvR <br>
&gt; which limits the usefulness of parry. The simple fact is that I very <br>
&gt; rarely hear the sound of a parry in RvR and I have 17 in parry for a <br>
&gt; parry chance of 13.5%.<br>
<br>
I think there is, but maybe reduced. I don't know what the issue is here, but there are persistent reports of some parry against styles.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufenrisfil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fenrisfil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/6/02 4:22:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> Very interesting. I don't think other realms get higher % bonus for their 2 handers though, because there two handers (well cd, and polearms at least) do a lot higher base damage anyway.<br>
<br>
The parry thing makes sense. <br>
<br>
Actually I'm not planning to spend much in parry, so will be very much an offensive based skald. I'm already using as many +qui items as I can, and as I usually group I don't have bt problems. I only use 1 handers for PvE against purples or if I have to be main tank. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/utralore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tralore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/9/02 2:23:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1 handed/shield or 2 handed and why?</span><hr size=1> I use the 2 handed I'd say 90% of the time, for the extra damage they give you in a fight, but that extra damage isn't always worth it.<br>
<br>
PVE: deep purples, damage adds are where your main damage comes in here, and you need the speed to do more damage here.<br>
<br>
RVR: This is my main point, when in RVR I ALWAYS have the shield up... it blocks not only ARROWS, but also I have it block BOLTS alot of the time.<br>
 If you are defending a keep or attacking a keep, I'd recommend putting one on, I swap to 2 handed as soon as I actually engage the enemy with it, then when he's dead swap back... After all, the 2 handed weapon only gives it's benifit while your swinging it, the shield helps while your in combat and out of immediate combat...<br>
<br>
So basically, when your in RVR, and not fighting carry the shield, soon as you get ready to swing, swap that baby to 2 hander and provoke that meany. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  then swap back. you get the best of both worlds this way.<br>
<br>
Another point, that has been mentioned already here, is the pulsing bubble casters, you need speed here, not slow and high damage. The extra attack that lands along with your damage add will do the more damage in the long run.<br>
<br>
Tralore Trashe<br>
Mid/Lancelot<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/10/02 7:10:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Parry</span><hr size=1> IIRC, there was supposed to be a bonus to 2 handed weapon users in parry, but the bonus was incorrectly set as a penalty (a minus instead of a plus), thus making 2handed weapon users parrying approx. half as often as they should be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/umightymouseman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MightyMouseMan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/10/02 3:04:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Parry</span><hr size=1> For RvR:  I agree that 2-handers do more damage, but they are much slower.... sooo....  If you run into a person running bladeturn, you will have a real hard time getting through with a slow weapon.<br>
<br>
